<em><strong>Neptune</strong></em> was the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Microsoft_codenames" class="postlink">codename</a> for a version of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Windows" class="postlink">Microsoft Windows</a> under development in 1999. Based on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_2000" class="postlink">Windows 2000</a>, it was to replace the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_9x" class="postlink">Windows 9x</a> series<sup><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Neptune#cite_note-3" class="postlink">[<br />3<br />]</a></sup> and was scheduled to be the first consumer version of Windows built on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_NT" class="postlink">Windows NT</a> code.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Neptune">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Neptune</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=831">JoshD</a> — Mon Jan 25, 2016 4:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
